\keepn \f12 \cf5 \fs36 \b \i [1] Introduction\par \b0 \i0 \pard \f12 \fs24 \pard \qc \f12 \b \cf0 WinDEU 5.24\b0 : Windows DOOM  Editor Utilities\par \par based on the code of\par DEU 5.21: DOOM  Editor Utilities\par \pard \par WinDEU is an extremely powerful Windows based editor that enables you to add your creativity to one of the most exciting PC games on the market...\par \par \qc \b D   O   O   M\par \b0 \'a9 id software\par \par \pard (Please read the file README.TXT first.  It contains important information about copyrights and trademarks.)\par \par WinDEU is based on the DEU 5.21 source code (for about 60%). The current version of WinDEU support \b DOOM1\b0 ,  \b DOOM 2\b0 , and \b HERETIC\b0 .\par \par This help file is based on the DEU 5.21 documentation file, and has been updated with WinDEU new features and dialog boxes.\par \par See also:\par \tab \uldb [1.1] Installing WindDEU\uldb0 \v Installing_WindDEU\v0 \par \tab \uldb [1.2] WinDEU Features\uldb0 \v WINDEU_FEATURES\v0 \par \par \page
${\footnote $ [1.1] Installing WindDEU}
#{\footnote # Installing_WindDEU}
+{\footnote + A:00001}
\keepn \f12 \fs24 \tx2265 \f12 \cf5 \fs36 \b \i [1.1] Installing WindDEU\par \b0 \i0 \pard \f12 \fs24 \pard \tx360 \fi-360 \li360 \cf0 There are currently two versions of WinDEU:\par \par \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab A Windows 3.1 (Win16) version, zipped in \f1 \fs18 W16DEU52.ZIP\f12 \fs24 .\par \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab A Windows NT (Win32) version, zipped in \f1 \fs18 W32DEU52.ZIP\f12 \fs24  . You need Windows NT or Win32s for Windows 3.1 to run this version. WinDEU32 is faster than WinDEU, thanks to 32-bit memory management.\par \par Instructions to install WinDEU:\par \par \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab Create a directory to install WinDEU\par \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab Unzip \f1 \fs18 W16DEU52.ZIP\f12 \fs24  (or \f1 \fs18 W32DEU52.ZIP\f12 \fs24 )\par \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab If you want 3D controls in the dialog boxes, copy the \f1 ctl3dv2.dll\f12  (and/or \f1 ctl3d32.dll\f12 ) file from the \f1 ctl3dll\f12  directory to your Windows system directory (usualy c:\\windows\\system).\par \fi-1800 \li2160 \i IMPORTANT\i0 :\tab Don't put the \f1 ctl3dv2.dll\f12  (and/or \f1 ctl3d32.dll\f12 ) in the WinDEU directory, or the 'dll' will tell you it's no correctly installed when you start WinDEU.\par \fi-360 \li360 \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab Edit the \f1 windeu.ini\f12  file to suit your configuration (entering your doom/doom2/heretic directory is essential).\par \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab Add an WinDEU program item in one of your program group.\par \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab RunWinDEU by clicking to program item.\par \f14 \'b7\f12 \tab If you are new to WinDEU, look at the 'Tutorial' in the help menu.\par \par \par See also:\par \pard \fi-360 \li360 \tab \uldb Starting WinDEU\uldb0 \v STARTING_WINDEU\v0 \par \pard \tx360 \fi-360 \li360 \par \fi0 \li0 \page
