K{\footnote K WinDEU Features}
K{\footnote K  Features}
\keepn \f12 \fs24 \f12 \cf5 \fs36 \b \i [1.2] WinDEU Features\par \b0 \i0 \pard \f12 \fs24 \pard \tx1605 \cf0 Full Function Level Editor\par \li396 Most doom structures can be edited. (Things, Vertices, Linedefs, Sidedefs, Sectors, Demos, more...)\par Create a Level From Scratch.\par Modify existing id levels or user created levels.\par *NEW* Contextual menus with Right mouse button.\par \li0  \par Special Features\par \li396 Insert a Predefined object\par \li792 Rectangle\par Nsided Polygon\par \li396 'DragnDrop' stretching and shrinking of sectors.\par Scale and rotate sectors, linedefs, vertices, or things.  \par Quickly define an area (selection box) and mass select everything in it.\par Sector floor/ceiling height distributor for easy stairways.\par *NEW* A toolbar with bubble tips\par *NEW* UNDO/REDO functions\par \li0  \par Diagnostic Tools\par \li396 Detects WAD errors.\par Warns you if you've forgotten player start things.\par Can automatically correct some problems.\par Use this to fix those problem wads, even if you created them with other editors.\par \pard \tx1170 \fi-792 \li1188 \b \i Note\b0 \i0 :\tab If the other editor uses nonstandard constructs you may not be able to take the WAD back to the other editor.\par \pard \tx1605  \par WAD File merging capability.\par \li396 Load and Merge multiple levels into a single WAD file.\par \li0  \par Import RAW data into DOOM object and save it in a PWAD.\par \par Renumber Maps to different Episodes and Levels.\par \par Much Much More!  \par \par \i Try it and see.  Just WinDEU it!\par \i0 \par \page
${\footnote $ [2] Starting WinDEU}
