K{\footnote K Starting WinDEU}
\keepn \f12 \cf5 \fs36 \b \i \f12 [2] Starting WinDEU\par \b0 \i0 \pard \f12 \fs24 \pard \cf0 WinDEU may be started by executing WinDEU in the Program Manager, or be creating an icon for the program. Sorry, but there's no "install" program yet.\par \par \pard \tx0 \tx735 \fi-792 \li792 \b \i Note\b0 \i0 :\tab \b VERY IMPORTANT\b0  for you guys who never read help files: WinDEU need to know where is the DOOM.WAD (or DOOM2.WAD) file. So, you *MUST* edit the \f1 \fs18 windeu.ini\f12 \fs24  file and modify the line "main=..." to set up the path of your Doom main wad file.\par \pard \fi-396 \li1188 Example:\tab \f1 \fs18 main=c:\\games\\doom\par \pard \f12 \fs24  \par WinDEU [options]\par \li396 Start WinDEU with the default IWAD file, DOOM.WAD and no PWADs.\par \pard  \par WinDEU [options] file <PWAD file> [<PWAD file>...]\par \li396 Start WinDEU with the default IWAD file and the PWAD file(s) given.\par \pard  \par WinDEU [options] w <IWAD file>\par \li396 Start DEU with the specified main IWAD file (DOOM.WAD or DOOM1.WAD).\par \pard \par See also:\par \tab \uldb [2.1] Command line parameters\uldb0 \v CMD_LINE_PARAMS\v0 \par \tab \uldb [2.2] Preferences settings\uldb0 \v PREFERENCES\v0 \par \tab \uldb [2.3] Initialization file\uldb0 \v WINDEU_INI\v0 \par \pard \tx0 \tx396 \tx792 \tx1188 \tx1584 \tx1980 \tx2376 \tx2778 \tx3174 \tx3570 \tx3966 \tx4362 \tx4758 \tx5154 \tx5556 \tx5952 \tx6348 \tx6744 \tx7140 \par \page
