\keepn \f12 \fs24 \f12 \cf5 \fs36 \b \i [2.3] Initialization file\par \cf1 \fs24 \b0 \i0 \pard \f12 \fs24 \pard \cf0 Rather than using command line arguments you may wish to save your typical settings in the \f1 WINDEU.INI\f12  file.  It's structure is pretty basic.  Use your favorite text editor to check it out.\par \par \pard \tx1080 \fi-1080 \li1080 \b \i Note\b0 \i0 :\tab The syntax of the \f1 WINDEU.INI\f12  file is a little bit different from the usual syntax of Windows INI file (i.e. comments are introduced by "#" instead of ";", no sections).\par \pard \li1080 This may be changed in future version of WinDEU, but, for now, WinDEU still uses the syntax of DEU initialization file.\par \pard \par ALL of the command line options may be used in \f1 WINDEU.INI\f12  with the exception of "help" and "config".  Commands in \f1 WINDEU.INI\f12  should be completely spelled out (i.e. quiet=true, not q=true)\par \par Also, don't put the "" in front of commands in the config file.\par \par And now your bonus for reading this far...\par \par Add the following line to your \f1 WINDEU.INI\f12  file:\par #*****************\par reminder1 = false\par #*****************\par \par This will turn off the opening reminder to read the documentation.\par \par \page
