\keepn \f12 \fs24 \f12 \cf5 \fs36 \b \i [4.2] Mouse Commands\par \b0 \i0 \pard \f12 \fs24 \pard \cf0 WinDEU use a *New* mouse interface. I made it to be like most Windows editing application.\par \par If you have a mouse, the following actions are available:\par \par Left mouse button (LMB)\par \li396 Mark the current selected object and unmark others.\par \pard  \par Shift + LMB\par \li396 Mark/Unmark an object (without unmarking other)\par \pard  \par LMB double click\par \li396 Edit seleted objects if pointer on an object.\par \pard  \par Right mouse button (RMB)\par \li396 Display context sensitive edit menu if pointer on an object, else display a general edit menu.\par \pard  \par Shift + RMB\par \li396 Center map around pointer\par \pard  \par Mouse move\par \li396 If LMB pressed:\par \li792 if pointer on an object, begin 'Drag mode'\par else, begin 'Stretch selection box' mode. If SHIFT key pressed, the selection box will be additive\par \li396 Else\par \li792 select new current object under mouse pointer (if CTRL key not pressed)\par \pard \par \fi-792 \li792 \b \i Note\b0 \i0 :\tab Try in the editor, and it will be easy to understand.\par \pard \par \page
