${\footnote $ Door step 1}
#{\footnote # Door_step_1}
+{\footnote + AS:00001}
\keepn \f12 \fs24 \f12 \cf5 \fs36 \b \i Door step 1\par \b0 \i0 \pard \f12 \fs24 \pard \cf0 The \uldb split linedef\uldb0 \v Split_LineDef_and_Add_new_Vertex\v0  feature can be used to add a vertex which can then be dragged to where you want the edge of the door to be.  This is helpful if you decide after you build the sector that you want to have a door.  If you planned ahead you won't need this.\par \par Add some vertices & lines to build a new sector which will later become the door.\par \par You may want to add some more vertices and lines to build a sector on the other side of the door so you've got somewhere to go once the door is open.\par \par \{s7.wad - linedefs and sectors\}\par \par There's no door here yet, but it'll be coming soon.\par Split line 0 into lines 0 & 8.\par Added lines 9,10,11.  Used lines 0,9,10,& 11 to add sector 2\par (Sector 2 will become the door in the next file.)\par Added lines 12,13,14.  Added sector 3 on lines 10,12,13,& 14.\par Sector 3 is the room on the other side.     \par \par Go to \uldb Door step 2\uldb0 \v Door_step_2\v0 \par \par \page
${\footnote $ Door step 2}
